g.title: cli
g.text: The library exposes a command line interface for main actions - build docs to json graph, gnerate visualization, query a generated graph by keywords

g.title: jsxRuntime
g.text: TSKB provides a custom JSX runtime (jsx-runtime module) that transforms TSX documentation syntax into a knowledge graph. Configured via tsconfig's jsxImportSource option, it processes JSX elements differently from React - instead of DOM rendering, it extracts documentation structure, references, and code snippets for analysis and visualization.

g.title: tsProgram
g.text: TypeScript compiler Program from source files and tsconfig settings that enables static analysis of code structure, types, and symbols without emitting JavaScript output.

g.title: registry
g.text: The global namespace (declare global { namespace tskb }) containing typed interfaces (Folders, Modules, Exports, Terms) that serve as a type-safe vocabulary registry, enabling autocomplete and type-checked references across all .tskb.tsx documentation files.

g.title: graph
g.text: Refers to th raw output of the library, where it constructs all the relations and connections between folders, modules, exports, terms, docs, etc. In its raw form it is a json file

g.title: dotFile
g.text: A Graphviz DOT format file that describes the graph structure with nodes and edges, used for rendering visual diagrams of the architecture

g.title: queryMatch
g.text: A structured result from querying the knowledge graph, containing the matched node, its hierarchy, relationships, related files, documentation context, and AI suggestions for next steps

g.title: ast
g.text: Abstract Syntax Tree - TypeScript's tree representation of source code, used by the compiler API to analyze code structure

g.title: declarationMerging
g.text: TypeScript feature that allows multiple declarations with the same name to be merged into a single definition, enabling distributed vocabulary across files

g.title: typeChecker
g.text: TypeScript compiler component that resolves types, validates code, and provides type information for symbols in the AST

g.title: literalType
g.text: A TypeScript type that represents a specific literal value (e.g., string literal 'hello' or number literal 42), used to extract constant values from type definitions

g.title: jsxElement
g.text:
A JSX syntax node in the TypeScript AST representing an element like or

, containing opening tag, children, and closing tag

g.title: jsxExpression
g.text: A TypeScript AST node representing an embedded expression in JSX curly braces like {ref as tskb.Folders['Auth']}

g.title: typeAssertion
g.text: TypeScript 'as' syntax that casts a value to a specific type, used in tskb to reference vocabulary items: {ref as tskb.Modules['X']}

g.title: depthFirstTraversal
g.text: Tree traversal algorithm that explores as far as possible along each branch before backtracking, used to visit all JSX nodes in order

g.title: globPattern
g.text: File pattern syntax (e.g., '**/*.tskb.tsx') used to match documentation files for processing
